tors with\nimproved specifications have the ability to provide a hint of such a signal\nwith a predicted significance up to $5.7\\sigma$ for galaxies and $1.6\\sigma$\nfor the cosmic shear. The bound on the dark matter lifetime attainable\nexploiting voids is predicted to improve on current bounds in a mass range for\nthe WIMP of $25\\div900$ GeV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 6 May 2022 16:50:30 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 10 Nov 2022 14:00:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-11-11"}
